                              <td class="encon"><p><strong><a name="II"></a>ARTICLE II.  MEMBERS</strong></p>                                
                                <p><strong>Categories of Membership and Rights</strong><br>
                                Section 2.01. The categories of membership shall be as follows:<br>
                                Membership of the AUCE shall consist of three categories:<br>
                                (a) Individual Membership.  Any individual who accepts the Constitution and the Bylaws of the organization and is willing to commit to the promotion of its goals and missions is qualified to apply for membership.  Acceptance of membership shall be subject to the approval of the Board of  Directors or such committee as designated by the Board from time to time.<br>
                                (b) Organizational Membership.  The term &quot;organizational membership&quot; shall refer to membership for all types of business entities including, but not limited to, corporations, educational and non-educational institutions, and trade associations, within or outside of the state of California.  Membership under this category shall be subject to payment of dues as provided under section 2.02 hereunder and approval by the Board of Directors or such committee as designated by the Board from time to time.<br>
                                (c) Honorary Membership. Any individual or business entity may be awarded honorary membership by reason of outstanding contributions in the promotion of the goals and missions of AUCE.  The criteria for awarding honorary membership shall be determined by the Board of Directors from time to time.</p>
                                <p><strong>Membership Dues</strong><br>
                                Section 2.02.<br>
                                Membership dues shall be as follows:<br>
                                (a)  Individual Membership:  Dues for individual membership shall not be required for the first fiscal year of  AUCE.  All individual membership dues beginning the first day of the second fiscal year shall be determined by the Board of Directors annually.  Notice to the members of any changes in dues shall be given by the Board to the members at least sixty days prior to the end of each fiscal year.  For the purpose of giving notice, the Board may post its due changes by means of electronic communication mechanisms, publications, or in such other manner as the Board deems appropriate.<br>
                                (b)  Organizational Membership.  Dues for organizational membership shall be Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00) and such additional contributions as may be volunteered by the member.  Organizational membership dues may be changed by the Board as it deems appropriate on an annual basis. Notice to the members of any subsequent changes in dues shall be given by the Board to the members at least sixty days prior to its due date.  For the purpose of giving notice, the Board may post its due changes by means of electronic communication mechanisms, publications, or in such other manner as the Board deems appropriate.<br>
                                (c)  Honorary Membership.  There shall be no dues required for this category of membership.</p>
                                <p><strong>Termination of Membership<br>
                                </strong>Section 2.03.<br>
                                The membership of any member shall terminate:<br>
                                (1) upon receipt by the Board or its officers of the member's written notice of termination.<br>
                                (2)  upon non-payment of dues.<br>
                                (3)  upon death of any individual member, or dissolution of the business entity of any organizational member.  Honorary membership shall be terminated upon resolution of the Board.<br>
                                Except as otherwise provided herein, any membership may be terminated by the Board upon its resolution for cause or without cause.</p>
                                <p><strong>Membership Record<br>
                                </strong>Section 2.04.  All membership records shall be maintained at principal place of business of the organization, and may be inspected by its members upon written request for legally permissible reasons.  Membership records shall not be used for any commercial or other reasons not in furtherance with the goals and missions of the organization.   All inspection requests must be submitted to the Board in writing for prior approval.  The Board shall have exclusive right to reject any and all membership record inspection request, and the decision by the Board shall be deemed final.</p>
                                <p><strong>Transferability of Membership<br>
                                </strong>Section 2.05. Membership in this organization is nontransferable and non-assignable.<br>
                                </p>                                </td>
