                              <td valign="top" class="encon"><p><strong><a name="IV"></a>ARTICLE IV. BOARD OF DIRECTORS</strong></p>
                                <p><strong>Qualifications</strong><br>
                                Section 4.01. Any Member, except Organizational Members, of this Association is qualified to be a Board of Director hereof.</p>
                                <p><strong>Election</strong><br>
                                Section 4.02. Board of Directors, other than those named in the Constitution, shall be elected in the annual meeting by the members, provided a quorum is present, or if no quorum is present, at the next succeeding special meeting at which a quorum is present, or other manner of election by ballot or by mail or by other reasonable means, and the candidates receiving the highest number of votes up to the number of Board of Directors to be elected are elected. Board of Directors, including the original Board of Directors, shall be eligible for reelection without limitation on the number of terms they may serve, provided they continue to meet the qualifications for office.</p>
                                <p><strong>Terms of Office</strong><br>
                                  Section 4.03.<br>
                                  (a) At the first annual meeting 1/3 of the Board of Directors named in the Constitution will be confirmed to serve a two-year term, 1/3 of the Board of Directors named in the Constitution will be confirmed to serve a three-year term, and 1/3 of the Board of Directors named in the Constitution will be confirmed to serve a four-year term.<br>
                                (b) Thereafter Board of Directors, other than those named in the Constitution, shall serve three-year terms from the time they are elected until the next annual election of Board of Directors and until theirs successors are elected.</p>
                                <p><strong>Duties</strong><br>
                                Section 4.04. It shall be the duty of the Board of Directors to perform any and all duties imposed on them collectively or individually by law, by the Constitution of this Association, or by these Bylaws.</p>
                                <p><strong>Compensation</strong><br>
                                Section 4.05. Board of Directors shall serve without compensation, except that they shall be allowed and paid their actual and necessary expenses incurred in attending Board of Directors?meeting or any other provision allowing partial compensation.</p>
                                <p><strong>Removal</strong><br>
                                Section 4.06. The entire Board of Board of Directors, or any individual Director, may be removed from office at any time by the vote of 2/3 of the members of the Association. If any or all Board of Directors are so removed, new Board of Directors may be elected to fill out the terms of the removed Board of Directors.</p>
                                <p><strong>Vacancies</strong><br>
                                Section 4.07. Vacancies caused by the death, resignation, disability of a Director or Board of Directors, or by his or their removal as provided in these Bylaws, or by an amendment of the Constitution increasing the number of Board of Directors authorized shall be filled by the members present at a Annual Meeting or Special Meeting of members called for that purpose, provided a quorum is present. Persons elected to fill vacancies as in this section provided shall hold office for the un-expired terms of their predecessors, or until their removal or resignation as in these Bylaws provided.</p>
                                <p><strong>Meetings</strong><br>
                                  Section 4.08. (a) The meeting of Board of Directors shall be presided over by a chairperson chosen by a majority of the Board of Directors present. The Secretary of the Association or, in his absence, any Director appointed by the presiding officer shall act as Secretary of the Board of Directors.<br>
                                (b) Every act or decision done or made by a majority of the Board of Directors present at a meeting duly held at which a quorum is present is the act of the Board of Directors, and hence of the Association, unless the Constitution or these Bylaws require a greater number or otherwise provide.</p>                              </td>
