                                <p>Section 7.01. The Board of Directors, by a majority vote, can establish an Advisory Board. A member of the Board should be a recognized expert in one of the scientific or technological areas or an internationally known scholar in the humanities or literature or a public figure who has made significant contributions in US-China relationships. The membership of a member of the Board of Advisors can be terminated at any time by the Board of Directors.<br>
