                                <p><strong>Adoption, Amendment, and Repeal</strong><br>
                                Section 8.01. These Bylaws shall become effective on their being signed by the original Board of Directors as named in the Constitution, or on their adoption by the vote or written consent of a majority of the voting members of this Association, and they may be amended or repealed, in whole or in part, and new Bylaws adopted by the vote or written consent of a majority of the voting members of the Association.</p>
                                <p><strong>Certification and Inspection</strong><br>
                              Section 8.02. The original or a copy of the Bylaws, as amended or otherwise altered to date, certified by the Secretary of the Association, shall be recorded and kept in a book which shall be kept in the principal office of the Association, and such book shall be open to inspection by the members at all reasonable times during office hours.</p></td>
