                                Section9.01. The Board of Directors shall cause a written annual report, including a financial statement, to be prepared and submitted to the members in the annual meeting of each year. The report shall summarize the associations activities for the preceding year and activities projected for the forthcoming year; the financial statement shall consist of a balance sheet as of the close of business of the corporations fiscal year, contain a summary of receipts and disbursements, be prepared in such manner and form as is sanctioned by sound accounting practices, and be certified by the Treasurer or a public accountant.</p>
                                <p><strong>Fiscal Year</strong><br>
